works.location: Wallace H. Coulter - Department of Biomedical Engineering
works.position: Graduate Research Assistant | Mentor: John N. Oshinski, PhD & Jason W. Allen, MD, PhD
works.description:
Quantify carotid artery hemodynamics using 4D flow MRI in patients with Carotid web (CaW):
                              o	Understand the blood hemodynamic alterations due to CaW.
                              o	Analyze 4D flow MRI data and compare it to CFD simulation. 
                              o	Quantify particle residence time and wall shear stress using 4D flow MR data. 
                              o	Correlate cryptogenic strokes risk in patients with CaW.
                          •	Determining Carotid Wall Thickness using TSE and STAR-MATCH MRI imaging sequence:
                              o	Develop an understanding of vessel wall imaging with different acquisition parameters.
                              o	Compare multiple imaging protocols (STAR-MATCH vs. TSE).
                              o	Evaluate image quality by calculating Contrast to noise ratio and image artifact grading. 
                          •	Predict virtual fractional flow reserve using computational flow dynamic (CFD):
                              o	Develop a deep understanding of the coronary artery and flow dynamics parameters. 
                              o	Use ANSYS Fluent program to perform CFD simulation for vFFR quantification.
